-- Svindal Wins World Cup Super-G Ski Title With Victory in Norway
-- B y   P e t e r - J o s e p h   H e g a r t y
-- 2013-03-03T14:46:55Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2013-03-03/svindal-wins-world-cup-super-g-ski-title-with-victory-in-norway.html
Aksel Lund Svindal won the men’s
World Cup super-G skiing title with his fifth victory of the
season before a home crowd in Kvitfjell, Norway.  Austria’s Georg Streitberger was second and Werner Heel of
Italy third today. Austria’s Marcel Hirscher still leads the
overall World Cup standings, with Svindal 29 points behind.  Anna Fenninger of Austria won the women’s super-G in
Garmisch-Partenkirchen, Germany, today, ahead of Maria Hoefl-
Riesch of Germany and Julia Mancuso of the U.S.  Super-G category leader  Tina Maze  of Slovenia, who’s
already assured of the overall title, was fourth.  Yesterday Maze set a World Cup skiing record for points in
a season by winning the downhill in Garmisch-Partenkirchen. She
has 2,074 points, with Hoefl-Riesch second on 1,050.  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
 Christopher Elser  at   celser@bloomberg.net . 